==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chronic
<hw>Chron"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>chronicus</ets>, Gr. <?/ concerning time, from <?/ time: cf. F.
<ets>chronique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to time;
according to time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Continuing for a long time; lingering;
habitual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chronic disease</b></col>, <cd>one which is inveterate,
of long continuance, or progresses slowly, in distinction from an
<xex>acute</xex> disease, which speedly terminates.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chronical</ent>⟦br⟧
